@startuml nav_state_to_ivi_backbone_nav_context_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Nav State To IVI Backbone Nav Context Signal Flow\n(CAN navigation state + route ETA -> IVI backbone nav-context publication)

participant "Navigation CAN state" as NavCan #F4F7FB
participant "Route ETA bus" as Route #E8F0FE
participant "IVI\nbackbone nav-context packager" as IVI #E8F7E8
participant "ETH nav-context frame" as EthNav #FFF4CC
participant "CGW / IBOX /\nbackbone consumers" as Consumers #FFF4CC

== IVI Inputs ==

NavCan -> IVI : frmNavModuleStateMsg\nNavRouteClass / NavGuideType /\nNavSpeedLimit / NavEtaMinutes
Route -> IVI : frmNavigationRouteMsg\nEtaMinutes
activate IVI
IVI -> IVI : roadZone = clamp(NavRouteClass)
IVI -> IVI : navDirection = clamp(NavGuideType)
IVI -> IVI : baseZoneContext =\nderiveBaseZoneContextFromNavState(roadZone, navDirection)
IVI -> IVI : zoneDistance =\nderiveZoneDistanceFromEtaMinutes(EtaMinutes)
IVI -> IVI : if roadZone > 0 and speedLimit == 0\nthen speedLimit = 30
note right of IVI
Representative derived fields
- roadZone
- navDirection
- zoneDistance
- speedLimit
- baseZoneContext
end note

== Backbone Publish ==

IVI -> EthNav : ethMsgNavContext\n(byte0 roadZone/navDirection,\nbyte1 zoneDistance,\nbyte2 speedLimit)
EthNav -> Consumers : backbone nav-context distribution
deactivate IVI

note over NavCan, Consumers
Representative runtime chain
1. CAN navigation state and route ETA reach IVI
2. IVI normalizes road zone, direction, speed limit, and zone distance
3. IVI publishes a compact backbone nav-context frame
4. CGW and downstream Ethernet consumers use the nav-context surface
end note

@enduml
